---
By: Epictetus
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 353
    Verse: 22
Tags:
  - Patience
---
Nothing great is created suddenly, any more than a bunch of grapes or a
fig. If you tell me that you desire a fig. I answer you that there must be
time. Let the tree first blossom, then bear fruit, then ripen.
